This should only be used by implementations of derived classes.
</para><variablelist role="params">
<varlistentry><term><parameter>stream</parameter>&#160;:</term>
<listitem><simpara>the <link linkend="EvaStream"><type>EvaStream</type></link> to affect.
</simpara></listitem></varlistentry>
</variablelist></refsect2>
<refsect2 id="eva-stream-mark-never-partial-reads" role="macro">
<title>eva_stream_mark_never_partial_reads()</title>
<indexterm zone="eva-stream-mark-never-partial-reads"><primary sortas="eva_stream_mark_never_partial_reads">eva_stream_mark_never_partial_reads</primary></indexterm><programlisting>#define             eva_stream_mark_never_partial_reads(stream)</programlisting>
<para>
Indicate that the <link linkend="eva-stream-read"><function>eva_stream_read()</function></link>
will always read a whole buffer of data.
</para><variablelist role="params">
<varlistentry><term><parameter>stream</parameter>&#160;:</term>
<listitem><simpara>the <link linkend="EvaStream"><type>EvaStream</type></link> to affect.
</simpara></listitem></varlistentry>
</variablelist></refsect2>
